  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients of both genders aging between 18-65 years with primary simple anal fistula
             (subcutaneous, intersphincteric, or low trans-sphicnteric involving less than 25% of
             external anal sphincter fibers)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with high trans-sphincteric, extra-sphincteric, supra-sphincteric, secondary,
             or recurrent anal fistulas.

          -  Patients with associated anorectal pathology such as anal fissure, hemorrhoids, rectal
             prolapse, neoplasm, solitary rectal ulcer, and inflammatory bowel diseases.

          -  Patients under chronic corticosteriod or immunosuppressive therapy.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
